1
00:01:08,240 --> 00:01:09,949
[Episode 17: 15 cm, right?]

2
00:01:15,719 --> 00:01:16,920
Did I wake you?

3
00:01:16,920 --> 00:01:18,560
I'll go sleep outside.

4
00:01:18,560 --> 00:01:19,841
It's fine.

5
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:14,267
What's wrong?

6
00:02:16,160 --> 00:02:17,593
There's a mosquito.

7
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:20,012
I'll go get the mosquito...

8
00:02:20,720 --> 00:02:22,039
It's gone.

9
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:41,759
Is the mosquito here again?

10
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:47,498
I can't fall asleep.

11
00:03:04,159 --> 00:03:07,039
Actually, I've made some preparations.

12
00:03:08,160 --> 00:03:10,742
But you might not be interested.

13
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:20,099
Can I sit next to you?

14
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:22,598
Sure.

15
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:25,677
It might take a while.

16
00:03:26,339 --> 00:03:28,040
A while?

17
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:29,809
That's good.

18
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:12,486
15 cm.

19
00:04:15,879 --> 00:04:17,334
This works too.

20
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:19,895
Are you sure?

21
00:04:22,080 --> 00:04:23,287
Yes.

22
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:36,252
She's willing to go because she trusts me.

23
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:40,111
There's no way I'm letting her down.

24
00:04:59,759 --> 00:05:02,864
Here are some books I read often.

25
00:05:02,864 --> 00:05:04,440
Pick one you like.

26
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:05,830
I'll read it to you.

27
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:08,730
This one.

28
00:05:18,279 --> 00:05:20,480
In early October 1815,

29
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:22,840
about an hour before sunset,

30
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:26,519
a traveler entered the small Dinie Town.

31
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:28,959
At this hour,

32
00:05:28,959 --> 00:05:30,907
only a few residents were still

33
00:05:31,520 --> 00:05:34,129
standing by the window or at the door.

34
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:41,217
They saw the traveler.

35
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:48,340
Ren Xi Zhou, 15 cm.

36
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:01,065
Are you asleep?

37
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:32,720
As inevitable as sunset is to sunrise,

38
00:06:32,720 --> 00:06:36,475
so too is death to life.

39
00:07:52,840 --> 00:07:54,340
You're awake?

40
00:07:57,330 --> 00:07:59,280
I just went out to buy breakfast.

41
00:07:59,280 --> 00:08:00,550
It's on the table.

42
00:08:00,550 --> 00:08:02,112
I'll get it for you.

43
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:07,577
I'm sorry.

44
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:11,322
Sorry for what?

45
00:08:11,959 --> 00:08:14,160
For waking up too late.

46
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:16,480
I'm the one who should be sorry.

47
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:18,455
I kept you up so late last night.

48
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,502
I'll go wash up.

49
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:47,176
It's okay. I was willing to do that.

50
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:03,640
So sweet. Give it a try.

51
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:11,846
Ren Xi Zhou!

52
00:09:12,559 --> 00:09:14,680
Low angle for the whole body.

53
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:17,305
High angle for the face.

54
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:29,934
Let me do it. You go stand there.

55
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:34,753
Ready? Three, two, one.

56
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:43,920
Idiot.

57
00:09:43,920 --> 00:09:45,102
Go.

58
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:53,874
Thanks.

59
00:09:58,559 --> 00:10:00,338
15 cm, right?

60
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:36,440
Look how big the sea is.

61
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:38,358
But Nanwan is so small.

62
00:10:39,440 --> 00:10:41,090
You want to leave here for college?

63
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:44,390
Yes, Mancheng University.

64
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:46,311
That's great.

65
00:10:47,040 --> 00:10:48,679
What about you?

66
00:10:48,679 --> 00:10:50,360
Mancheng University.

67
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:51,840
Even better.

68
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:53,200
We're hometown friends.

69
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:55,487
We can help each other out there.

70
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:02,527
Is that all?

71
00:11:03,759 --> 00:11:05,386
Just hometown friends?

72
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:10,013
Xiang Nan Feng.

73
00:11:10,680 --> 00:11:12,026
Let's go.

74
00:11:17,799 --> 00:11:19,808
They say a typhoon will hit tomorrow evening.

75
00:11:21,039 --> 00:11:22,759
We're lucky then.

76
00:11:22,759 --> 00:11:24,624
We're going home tomorrow.

77
00:11:24,624 --> 00:11:26,040
Yes.

78
00:11:26,040 --> 00:11:28,744
But remember the 15 cm rule.

79
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:12,442
It's so quiet.

80
00:12:39,697 --> 00:12:40,720
Hello?

81
00:12:40,720 --> 00:12:41,880
<i>Hello, Mr. Xiang.</i>

82
00:12:41,880 --> 00:12:43,919
<i>The producer has read your script.</i>

83
00:12:43,919 --> 00:12:46,200
<i>He's near your hometown now</i>

84
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:48,279
<i>and would like to meet up for a chat.</i>

85
00:12:48,279 --> 00:12:50,320
When and where?

86
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:53,050
<i>Tonight, at Haicheng Restaurant.</i>

87
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:57,159
There's a typhoon tonight.

88
00:12:57,159 --> 00:12:58,480
Is another time possible?

89
00:12:58,480 --> 00:13:00,254
<i>Huh? Wait a moment.</i>

90
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:02,920
<i>Sorry, Mr. Xiang.</i>

91
00:13:02,920 --> 00:13:04,640
<i>The producer really wants to meet tonight.</i>

92
00:13:04,640 --> 00:13:08,520
<i>We can arrange a hotel for you if needed.</i>

93
00:13:08,520 --> 00:13:10,440
<i>Honestly, if it speeds up the project signing,</i>

94
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:11,960
<i>we'll have to go,</i>

95
00:13:11,960 --> 00:13:14,436
<i>whether it's a typhoon or a hailstorm.</i>

96
00:13:16,159 --> 00:13:18,206
Got it. Thank you.

97
00:13:22,039 --> 00:13:23,399
What a mess.

98
00:13:23,399 --> 00:13:24,879
Why can't they just live peacefully?

99
00:13:24,879 --> 00:13:26,759
They had a huge argument yesterday.

100
00:13:26,759 --> 00:13:28,919
[Hongxia Diner]
Her daughter has a bad temper.

101
00:13:28,919 --> 00:13:31,720
Good thing she wasn't around, or...

102
00:13:31,720 --> 00:13:32,879
What are you talking about?

103
00:13:32,879 --> 00:13:34,760
Let me in on it.

104
00:13:34,760 --> 00:13:36,425
Come on, let's go.

105
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:39,120
<i>According to weather reports,</i>

106
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:40,600
<i>a strong typhoon is rapidly approaching</i>

107
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:42,600
<i>the southeast coast of our country.</i>

108
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:46,754
- Mom!
<i>- It's expected to hit Nanwan tonight.</i>

109
00:13:46,754 --> 00:13:47,559
Mom!

110
00:13:47,559 --> 00:13:49,240
<i>The wind near the center</i>

111
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:51,320
- Mom!
<i>- can reach force 8-9,</i>

112
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:53,394
<i>with gusts possibly exceeding force 9.</i>

113
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:55,620
Mom!

114
00:13:59,200 --> 00:14:00,356
Mom!

115
00:14:03,639 --> 00:14:04,848
Mom!

116
00:14:06,679 --> 00:14:07,930
Mom!

117
00:14:10,960 --> 00:14:12,023
Mom!

118
00:14:13,480 --> 00:14:15,156
Are you in there?

119
00:14:19,240 --> 00:14:20,465
Mom!

120
00:14:26,160 --> 00:14:27,403
Mom!

121
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:37,320
What happened? Where's my mom?

122
00:14:37,320 --> 00:14:40,000
<i>Your mom said not to tell you. I don't dare.</i>

123
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,602
Then forget about your pay.

124
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:43,745
<i>Your dad came back.</i>

125
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:45,639
How is that possible?

126
00:14:45,639 --> 00:14:47,320
He's working abroad.

127
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:49,919
We just had a video call last week. You...

128
00:14:49,919 --> 00:14:52,720
<i>It seems he lost money in business.</i>

129
00:14:52,720 --> 00:14:54,759
<i>And he wanted to mortgage the house.</i>

130
00:14:54,759 --> 00:14:56,639
<i>He had a big fight with your mom.</i>

131
00:14:56,639 --> 00:14:58,840
<i>Your mom told me to leave, so I did. And then--</i>

132
00:14:58,840 --> 00:15:00,157
Xi Zhou.
